The paper discusses joint precoding with finite rate feedback in a network MIMO setting, which involves communication theory and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with distributed channel state information, which involves networking and communication, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses precoding schemes and optimization, which could fall under cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.SY (Control and Systems Engineering). Finally, the paper deals with multi-user MIMO channels, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
